      • isSecondaryType

        public boolean isSecondaryType(SiteTypeEnum type)
        Checks if this type can support a secondary type of the one provided. This only iterates through the array. Since the array is generally empty or only has 1 or 2 entries, it doesn't seem worth it to create a set, as O(n) of only 1 or 2 is still O(1).
        Parameters:
        type - The type to check if this site type supports it as secondary.
        Returns:
        True if this is a primary type that supports type, or false otherwise.

      • getPrimaryPinName

        public java.lang.String getPrimaryPinName(java.lang.String secondaryPinName)
        Provides the secondary site type pin mapping to the primary pin name.
        Parameters:
        secondaryPinName - Name of the pin to check
        Returns:
        The primary pin name (which is often the same name of the pin provided)

      • getSecondaryPinName

        public java.lang.String getSecondaryPinName(java.lang.String primaryPinName)
        It this site type is secondary, it gets the corresponding pin name for a given primary pin name.
        Parameters:
        primaryPinName - The primary pin name with a potential secondary pin name.
        Returns:
        The pin name for this site type (if it is a secondary type) that corresponds to the primary type pin name. Returns null if this is not a secondary type and the provided pin is not a site pin.
